JIMMY:
* C-Come on

17:05.692 --> 17:08.195
* Yeah, yeah

17:08.228 --> 17:10.163
* Yeah, yeah

17:10.197 --> 17:11.798
(whooping)

17:19.372 --> 17:21.208
Some old lady told me
to give this to you.

17:21.241 --> 17:24.377
That's nice.

17:24.411 --> 17:27.247
Hey, there's a couple
hundred bucks in here.

17:27.280 --> 17:28.715
It's bar mitzvah money.

17:28.748 --> 17:30.217
It's the first major payday
for a Jewish kid.

17:30.250 --> 17:32.252
With sound
investment strategy,

17:32.285 --> 17:34.087
some people turn that
into a nice little nest egg.

17:34.121 --> 17:35.622
I'm getting a Jet Ski.

17:35.655 --> 17:37.690
Why didn't my parents
tell me about this?

17:37.724 --> 17:40.227
They probably wanted you to do
it for the right reasons.

17:40.260 --> 17:41.428
You know, I thought
I knew my parents.

17:41.461 --> 17:43.763
Maybe I didn't give them
enough credit.

17:48.668 --> 17:50.637
(laughs)

17:50.670 --> 17:52.239
What the hell
are you guys doing?

17:52.272 --> 17:54.307
We're just welcoming
your guests, honey.

17:54.341 --> 17:55.642
You got a card
from the Bronsteins.

17:55.675 --> 17:56.643
Oh.

17:56.676 --> 17:59.112
Oh, dog with a "yar-mulkay."

17:59.146 --> 18:00.347
Funny.

18:01.348 --> 18:02.582
Where's the money?

18:02.615 --> 18:03.650
We know you've been stealing.

18:03.683 --> 18:05.218
We're not stealing anything.

18:05.252 --> 18:06.619
It's our money.

18:06.653 --> 18:08.655
Easy, honey,
we've come too far.

18:08.688 --> 18:10.590
What do you mean
"come too far"?

18:10.623 --> 18:12.459
Give me that money!
Burt, stop it!

18:12.492 --> 18:15.595
It's my money. I'm the one
getting bar mitzvahed.

18:15.628 --> 18:17.764
No, it's not, 'cause
you're not really Jewish.

18:17.797 --> 18:19.432
We made this whole thing up.

18:23.303 --> 18:25.238
Oi veh.

18:30.310 --> 18:32.212
What do you mean
I'm not Jewish?

18:32.245 --> 18:33.446
Okay.

18:33.480 --> 18:35.815
This may sound a little bit
selfish, but

18:35.848 --> 18:39.252
we came up with this great idea
to raise money for a cruise.

18:40.353 --> 18:41.754
Would that be a cruise to hell?

18:41.788 --> 18:43.456
Because I think that's where
you two are going.

18:43.490 --> 18:45.592
Look, Burt, for years

18:45.625 --> 18:47.827
your father and I have been
invited to weddings,

18:47.860 --> 18:49.429
graduations, bar mitzvahs.

18:49.462 --> 18:51.698
We've spent thousands
of dollars on gifts

18:51.731 --> 18:54.434
for our friends and their
horrible children.

18:54.467 --> 18:56.336
Oh, it's the Weinbergs.

18:56.369 --> 18:58.171
Thank you for sharing
our special day.

18:58.205 --> 18:59.506
You see them?

18:59.539 --> 19:02.209
Five kids-- they breed
like they're Irish.

19:02.242 --> 19:05.212
I mean, we laid out cash
for five bar mitzvahs,

19:05.245 --> 19:06.546
five graduations,
and five weddings.

19:06.579 --> 19:08.315
And you never even had one.

19:08.348 --> 19:09.949
This is a payback to us, son.

19:09.982 --> 19:11.318
Please don't blow it for us.

19:11.351 --> 19:12.485
*

19:12.519 --> 19:14.221
Sounds like
they're starting.

19:14.254 --> 19:15.655
Oh, make us proud,

19:15.688 --> 19:16.856
bubeleh.

19:16.889 --> 19:18.291
Have a good bar mitzvah.

19:21.228 --> 19:22.662
I can't believe
I was trying to get

19:22.695 --> 19:24.197
those schmendriks
to like me.

19:24.231 --> 19:25.498
You should go up there
and expose

19:25.532 --> 19:28.501
their whole meshugana scheme
to everyone.

19:28.535 --> 19:30.370
No.

19:30.403 --> 19:31.671
This is still my bar mitzvah.

19:31.704 --> 19:33.406
All these people came
to hear me.

19:33.440 --> 19:35.308
And for the first time
in my life,

19:35.342 --> 19:36.709
I'm gonna finish
what I started.

19:41.414 --> 19:43.716
So, I'd like to thank all of you
for coming here

19:43.750 --> 19:45.818
to share this
special day with me.

19:45.852 --> 19:47.354
But first,

19:47.387 --> 19:51.258
I have something I have
to say to my parents.

19:51.291 --> 19:52.825
I haven't exactly had
big events in my life

19:52.859 --> 19:54.494
that were worthy
of celebration.

19:54.527 --> 19:56.996
And I know that, uh,

19:57.029 --> 20:00.233
knocking up
my high school girlfriend...

20:00.267 --> 20:02.369
...and giving you
a great-grandchild

20:02.402 --> 20:05.238
whose mother
is a serial killer,

20:05.272 --> 20:07.540
aren't exactly reasons
to rent out a hall

20:07.574 --> 20:08.875
and have a chocolate fountain.

20:08.908 --> 20:11.010
So...

20:11.043 --> 20:13.913
I do this for you now.

20:13.946 --> 20:15.382
I love you.

20:15.415 --> 20:16.716
We're even.

20:18.451 --> 20:20.320
And so we begin.

20:24.291 --> 20:28.261
"Barutch atta adonay."

20:28.295 --> 20:31.264
Uh...moustache
with a squiggly line,

20:31.298 --> 20:32.299
"H" with a tail.

20:32.332 --> 20:34.301
"E-lo-hei-nu."

20:34.334 --> 20:35.935
El, el, hey, you.

20:35.968 --> 20:38.405
JIMMY: My dad
may have struggled,

20:38.438 --> 20:39.972
but he didn't give up,

20:40.006 --> 20:42.542
even when the rabbi corrected
every word he said

20:42.575 --> 20:43.910
for over three hours.

20:43.943 --> 20:47.414
L.O.L.
It's like a marathon.

20:47.447 --> 20:48.648
You don't have to win.

20:48.681 --> 20:50.383
The accomplishment
is finishing.

20:50.417 --> 20:53.953
And I've never been
more proud of my dad.

20:53.986 --> 20:55.922
That was amazing, Dad.

20:55.955 --> 20:58.658
And to think, you did all that
and you're not even Jewish.

20:58.691 --> 21:00.427
I'm sorry.

21:00.460 --> 21:03.730
Did you say
he's not Jewish?

21:03.763 --> 21:06.433
Funny story, Rabbi.

21:06.466 --> 21:10.069
* My goyim parents
told a little fib... *

21:10.102 --> 21:11.471
Bup-bup-bup-bup-
bup-bup-bup-bup.

21:11.504 --> 21:13.473
You've wasted
enough of my time.

21:13.506 --> 21:15.475
Shalom, sir.
But, Rabbi...

21:15.508 --> 21:17.377
I said shalom.

21:20.980 --> 21:24.384
Okay, the Jewish thing's
officially over.

21:24.417 --> 21:26.619
Everybody back to our house
for some honey-glazed ham.

